<br>
I have only killed Diablo with Barbarian characters and then I used leap attack a lot. I tried jumping in to hit and then out to avoid his attacks. And I do believe I was about lev 30 at that time.<br>
Even then killing Diablo involved a lot of dieing. Just cast a tp before you engage and wear him out. Not an elegant way to do it, but it works.<br>
<br>
Concerning stats for the druid I am not sure. Most ppl go either Shapeshift/Summon or Elemental/Summon. To try both may be very hard, both concerning skillpoints and statpoints.<br>
<br>
The S/S needs Str and Vit and the E/S needs Energy and Vit. If you try to cover all three you may ending up having too little of everything to be able do live through NM and Hell. (Not that I have tried Hell yet, but it's a big step up to NM). <br>
<br>
As for how much in each, check out the requirtements for the armour and/or weapons you will be using when you are at the end game and plan accordingly.<br>
<br>
And most skills need a lot of skillpoints to be useful later on. A shapeshifter for example often maxes out both Lycantropy, Were- wolf/bear one spirit and at least one attack skill. Add a fair number of points in spirit-/direwolves and Grizzly and you will find you dont have many points left.<br>
<br>
I dont know if you have checked out any sites but I have a few favourite you may wanna check out.<br>
<br>
